# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Build output
**/dist/

# Environment & secrets
.env
.env.*

# OS
.DS_Store

# Debug logs
npm-debug.log*

# TypeScript
*.tsbuildinfo

# Deprecated (archived, don't track changes)
_deprecated/

# Claude Code
.claude/settings.local.json

# Python
__pycache__/
**/venv/
**/.venv/

# Generated data files
*.db
*.csv
*.pdf
*.log
# Atomic-write crash artifacts (learn_agent.py mkstemp tmps) + the regenerable
# ecosystem-kb mining watermark. The archive ITSELF (profile-history-archive.jsonl)
# is deliberately tracked — it's the only durable copy of evicted profile facts,
# consistent with profile.json being tracked in this private repo.
pa/data/*.tmp
pa/data/profile-history-archive.kb-watermark.json

# Secrets
**/credentials.json
**/google-token.json
**/secrets.env

# Editor
.obsidian/

# Root repo hygiene scratch/state
/.codex/
/pa/blackboard.json
# Generated reports at root (brain-recheck / audits — regenerated, not source)
/*_report.md
/brain_recheck_report.md

# === Repo-root hygiene: nothing personal/ephemeral lives at the root ===
# See docs/CONVENTIONS.md (public) + CLAUDE.md "Repository hygiene" (private).
# Repo root is reserved for repo-level files only: README, LICENSE, CLAUDE.md,
# optional MEMORY.md, BACKLOG.md, DEBUGGING.md, AGENTS.md/GEMINI.md aliases,
# .gitignore*, git-public.*. Anything else gets caught by the patterns below.

# External imports at root (PDFs, images, binaries — likely Telegram attachments)
/*.jpg
/*.jpeg
/*.png
/*.gif
/*.pdf
/*.db
/*.csv
/*.xlsx
/*.docx

# Email/conversation exports at root
/*_email_*.txt
/*_export_*.*
/*turns*.json
/*turns*.jsonl
/*turns*.txt
/extracted_facts.md

# Root is sparse — no code lives here (see CLAUDE.md hygiene). Ignore ALL
# root-level Python so ad-hoc / personal-data scripts can't be committed by
# accident — this closes the analysis.py-class gap that prefix patterns
# (/analyze_*.py, /check_*.py, ...) silently missed. Real scripts live in
# pa/scripts/ or projects/*/scripts/; throwaways go in scratch/.
/*.py
/check*.ps1
/scratch_*
# Worker/agent artifact: coding CLIs occasionally create this brain-bootstrap
# trigger file (referenced only in the global ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md protocol) in
# subdirectories they work in — recurred 3x during 2026-07 agent sessions.
**/.claude-needs-brain
/all_files.txt
/out*.txt
*.bak

# Misplaced Ecosystem KB schema files at repo root (canonical home is in your
# Obsidian vault / KB directory outside this repo, configured per-deployment).
# These are the standard filenames used by the `ecosystem-kb` skill.
/Action\ Items.md
/Preferences.md
/Financial.md
/People\ &\ Contacts.md
/Health\ &\ Medical.md

# LLM-agentic scratch writes: a worker occasionally "goes agentic" and writes
# its response/analysis to a local file at cwd instead of returning it as
# text or using its proper output path (run_brief.py has a documented retry
# for this exact failure mode). No application code writes these filenames —
# confirmed via full-repo grep 2026-07-09. If a new one recurs, add it here.
/message_to_user.md
/output.json
/skill_proposals.json

# Scratch workspace — for ad-hoc / WIP / throwaway files (see scratch/README.md)
/scratch/*
!/scratch/.gitkeep
!/scratch/README.md

# Inside any project: scratch + temp/debug-prefixed artifacts
**/scratch/
**/temp_*.py
**/temp_*.json
**/temp_*.md
**/temp_*.txt
**/debug_*.py
**/debug_*.log
**/*-debug.log
**/test_repro.*
**/test_real_login.*

# Large input data dirs
src_pdfs/

# Per-project data dirs — raw inputs, processed outputs, exports. Regenerated
# from source and often personal/sensitive (e.g. financial statements); must
# stay out of version control. config/ under data/ is intentionally NOT ignored.
**/data/raw/
**/data/processed/
**/data/exports/
**/data/prompt_processed/
# Bulk extracts / caches / generated outputs (large + personal; regenerated)
**/data/openai_history/
**/data/full_openai_extract/
**/data/files_zip_extract/
**/data/dalle_zip_extract/
**/data/simulations/
**/data/legacy_output/
**/data/query-results/
**/data/market_cache/

# Daily-mail-brief runtime artifacts (fetched email payloads + regenerated
# brief inputs/outputs — personal, recreated each run)
projects/daily-mail-brief/emails.json
projects/daily-mail-brief/analysis_input.md
projects/daily-mail-brief/briefing_output.md

# === Public-repo coexistence ===
# Separate .git directory + wrapper for the public framework repo
/.git-public/
/.gitignore-public
/git-public.cmd
/git-public.ps1

# Public-only files (untracked by private repo to avoid pollution)
/README.md
/LICENSE
/docs/
/examples/

# === OAuth artifact hygiene (prevent recurrence of auth_code leak) ===
**/auth_code.txt
**/auth_url*.txt
**/auth_*.txt

# === Temp / debug-only files that have leaked before ===
projects/daily-mail-brief/temp_brief.md
projects/daily-mail-brief/temp_*.py

# === User-personalized prompts (do not auto-stage in public clones) ===
# bot-instructions.md is the static system prompt appended to claude/zclaude spawns
# via --append-system-prompt-file. Each user customizes it locally.
# The private repo's existing tracked copy is unaffected — gitignore only
# prevents NEW additions in fresh clones (e.g. of the future public repo).
projects/telegram-bot/bot-instructions.md
